main event: Unidentified object observed by U.S. Marine Corps personnel near Route 1 at Kotzebue, Alaska on February 26, 1962.
interesting points: The object was initially described as a stationary glowing red object before it moved rapidly horizontally., The object had a cylindrical shape, estimated to be 20-30 feet in diameter and about 10 feet high., It was observed for approximately 5-15 minutes by witnesses., 6 different individuals, including military personnel, witnessed the sighting., FAA and NORAD reported no negative air traffic or balloon activity in the area at the time of the sighting.
witness description: U.S. Marine Corps personnel and civilians in Kotzebue
